# AI-Learning Repo — Git & Push Rules

## Git Identity

This repo uses **local** git config for the personal account `JayAI623`.
Do NOT change global git config when working in this repo.

- `user.name` = JayAI623
- `user.email` = (from ~/.gitconfig-personal)
- `github.user` = JayAI623

## Push via HTTPS (not SSH)

The SSH key belongs to JayLiuMLP (work), so `git push origin` will fail.
Always push using HTTPS with the JayAI623 token:

```bash
TOKEN=$(GITHUB_TOKEN= gh auth token)
git push https://JayAI623:${TOKEN}@github.com/JayAI623/AI-learning.git <branch>
```

## gh CLI Commands

Prefix with `GITHUB_TOKEN=` to use JayAI623's keyring auth:

```bash
GITHUB_TOKEN= gh pr create --repo JayAI623/AI-learning --base master ...
GITHUB_TOKEN= gh pr list --repo JayAI623/AI-learning
```

## Project Conventions

- Each visualizer: `<name>/index.html`, `<name>/css/page.css`, `<name>/js/app.js`
- Shared styles/utils go in `common/`
- Code and comments in English, respond to user in 中文
